{"lastModified":1751633482005,"uri":"c::7580644653::vessel::d5cc7823-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744","yachtType":["Motor"],"description":"Operating Area: France, Italy, Corsica, Sardinia, Monaco\n\n\nGroundbreaking, spacious and contemporary, presenting M.Y Wyldecrest, the first ever Sunseeker Ocean 90 to enter the charter market.\n\nHer unique and innovative design with plum bow offers unrivalled volume for her size, presenting beautifully designed entertaining spaces and expansive guest quarters perfect for special family holidays and group breaks.\n\nThe first of the new Ocean Club line of Sunseeker superyachts, she offers four times the area of a traditional bathing platform design. Complete with a barbecue and showers, the high-low platform Ocean Club also boasts ‘X-Tend’ reclining seats, which allow for extra sunbathing space by extending the aft deck in an all new design concept. The aft deck also features a retractable screen for extra privacy.\n\nAnother standout area of Wyldecrest is her foredeck and outdoor cinema. Her unusually wide bow creates a great additional space for sunbathing and relaxation during the day, but especially at night, when the cinema can be used against the night sky and ocean, resulting in a magical atmosphere.\n\nUp on the flybridge is the repeat helm console and multiple entertaining areas. The carbon fibre hardtop features a huge sliding canopy, offering the option for sun or shade as required. The fully equipped wetbar features a raised shelf and bar stools as well as bar style refrigerators and an ice maker. Aft, there is an additional open area for guests to enjoy as they wish with four comfortable sun loungers.\n\nInside, the main salon is voluminous and contemporary with fully glazed, floor to ceiling windows, resulting in a bright and airy living space. The galley features bar stools and sliding doors, giving the option of an open or concealed cooking area.\n\nFour modern and stylish cabins are located below deck, accessible by two separate staircases. The VIP cabin is forward with the master, double and a twin located amidships. The master features a mirror TV and wonderful contemporary artwork and truly benefits from the yacht’s wide beam, with previously unseen levels of space. The large ensuite features his and her sinks and a walk-in triple sized shower, complete with a waterfall showerhead. The VIP cabin is also extremely spacious and features a vanity mirror, 50 inch TV and an ensuite with a double shower and feature mirrors.\n\nThe two equal sized guest cabins are accessed amidships, one double and one twin with beds that can be conveniently converted to a double to suit each party’s requirements. They feature a full-size mirror, wardrobe and both have a port light within the window allowing plenty of fresh air and natural light, with a 50 inch TV in each cabin.\n\nWyldecrest is fully air-conditioned throughout with WiFi, a top of the range Sonos sound system and has stabilizers both at anchor and underway for smooth sailing. She also features a varied selection of water toys and equipment including a Williams 460 RIB tender, two F5 Cayago Seabobs, two paddle boards, a Sea-Doo Waverunner jetski, snorkel equipment and towable inflatables. Crew quarters accommodate up to four crew members in two twin cabins.","blueprint":{"name":"WYLDECREST","images":["/media/media::image::c::7580644653::vessel::d5cc7823-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::f4136ba0-fdb7-11ee-97a5-974eaebb841c.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::7580644653::vessel::d5cc7823-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::f5ed34b0-fdb7-11ee-97a5-974eaebb841c.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::7580644653::vessel::d5cc7823-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::f4925fa0-fdb7-11ee-97a5-974eaebb841c.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::7580644653::vessel::d5cc7823-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::f528ac30-fdb7-11ee-97a5-974eaebb841c.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::7580644653::vessel::d